<p align="center"><font color="#0E024D" face="Arial"><strong>PLAYER SUBMITTED STRATEGY</strong></font></p>
<div align="center"><center>

  <div align="center"><center><table border="0" width="90%">
    <tr>
      <td>
      <center><font face="Arial"><strong><b><font color="#800000">THE ART OF MURDER</b></font> - <small>StormWielder DragonHeart, Povar</small></strong></font><font face="Arial"></center>
<div align="center"><center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="80%">
  <tr>
    <td>
    <small><hr size="1" color="#C0C0C0"><P>
    Peace, Harmony, and Mass Murder
<p>
RULE NUMBER 1 : CHEAT in the PREFIGHT!!! Say, "Self-buffs only." Then say "ok, buffin self, then Im kickin your ass." Your sneaking this in and 99.9% of the time, they will not think of the fact that youre buffing yourself pre-fight which is totally to your advantage. Let them buff themselves too. No one buffs like a shaman. ADVANTAGE: SHAMAN. DO NOT do this if youre fighting a necro. If youre fighting a necro, insist that all buffing must be done during battle. You dont want DMF screwing up your DoT's. If your adversary has a pet, insist that pets are to be made during battle and not beforehand. If your adversary is an enchanter, a shadowknight, or does not have a pet, try to sneak your pet into the prefight buffing.
Always make  Chloroplast the last buff you cast on yourself.

<p> vs. Melee Types
<p>
Spell Lineup: 1. Greater Heal 2. Root 3. Flash of Light(yes, the level 1 spell) 4. highest DD spell 5. Invisibility 6. Highest poison spell 7. Highest disease spell 8. Spirit of Wolf
<p> Try to get them to challenge you. Then you control your distance when you type /duel  .... type it, but dont hit enter yet, run around, get good seperation from him, at the same time you hit enter,  cast Flash of Light.
<p> Continue casting flash of light until they are blind, then cast root. These are both low mana spells, so you can use them a hell of alot if necessary. If the guy is hitting you, dont bother with root yet, just cast flash of light until he is blind , then back up.
<p> Cast your highest level Disease and Poison spells.
<p> watch them die slowly. If he comes after you, just run around or reapply flash of light.
<p> if they are still alive, recast your poison spell or finish with a nuke. (In the case of the paladin using Lay on Hands, simply keep using your highest level poison spell every 40 seconds.

<p>  vs. Casters
<p> Spell lineup: 1. Greater Heal 2. Root 3. Flash of Light(yes, the level 1 spell) 4. highest DD spell 5. Invisibility 6. Highest poison spell 7. Highest disease spell 8. Spirit of Wolf
<p> Again, try to get them to challenge you. Since you are the most brutish of the casters, you can take a punch and have a nice interrupting skill (slam) Unlike melee classes, you want to get within melee range when you accept the duel. 
<p> Have autoattack already on before you type /duel. He wont notice. As you hit enter, again cast Flash of light and hit SLAM as soon as you see him start to cast a spell.
<p> Run like hell while he's blind. Get to the point right outside spell casting range. Keep casting flash of light while you run, so you know exactly when youre out of range (youre interrupting yourself by casting while running, so you wont be losing mana, just determining your distance.
<p> Step just inside casting range. Cast your highest level disease and poison spells. Then get back out of range and sit; watching for your opponent to break blind and finally spot you in the distance. But he's dying already. Unless he's a healing class, he wont survive, and all you have to do is keep away from him, either by rooting him and staying out of range or by kiting him. (SoW beats Jboots' azz)

<p> Special Cases
<p> Fighting a necro - NEVER fight close to a necro. Lifetap spells will kick your butt real fast. You want to fight a necro at the edge of the casting range. If the fool isnt using lifetap, do whatever you have to do, you cant lose.
<p> Fighting a cleric - fights against clerics have to be fast. When your opponent is half dead by the dot's, start nuking. Nuke until dead. DO NOT wait or kite a Cleric
<p> Enchanters - these folks have no hit points, but have alot of spells that just jack you up. The weakness of an enchanter is his hit points, so attack him there. Stay FAR away from an enchanter as well. You DO NOT want to be mezzed. Again, blind and playing with the casting range is great. Use DoT's quickly and stay out of his casting range.
<p> OTHER TIPS DURING A DUEL
<p> ALWAYS kill your opponent. Unless he can make it to a zone, he's dead. No one bubble stuff. You dont want your name displayed on the loser side when he comes back to jack you in an hour. Never believe "ok stop, Im zoning." Kill everyone.
<p> If your fighting near water against a caster, stand in it. Step forward on the shore to cast, then get back in the water; even if just your feet are in the water, the spell wont effect you, he loses all the mana from it, and doesnt get a message saying it didnt take effect. It looks to him as though he hit you, and he's burning all his mana, which is always nice.
<p> When in doubt... invis and go med. If youre losing, blind with Flash of Light, then go invisible and meditate in a cubbyhole or underwater. Heal yourself and come back and finish him. Casters lose all hope when theyre half dead from Dot's and they see your hp refreshing.
<p> ALWAYS ALWAYS ALWAYS invite the person into a group when your dueling. That way, if your switching between healing yourself , you dont have to go find him to target him, just hit f2 and fire.
<p> If youre out of range, let him come to you!  Never take your eyes off your opponent, and between casts, when youre sitting outside of casting range, keep pressing Flash of Light. It wont cost you mana and will go off the second he enters the casting area. The casting time on Flash of Light is NIL, so take advantage.
<p> Whether kiting an opponent, or just staying out of range, ALWAYS have him in your sights. You dont want the necro running out of your vision and medding or lifetapping some local mobs and using your own "out of range" tactic against you. 


<p>  Remember... The class can be played well, or played poorly. In a battle among similar levels,  strategy is the decisive factor in a fight. Without it, your just another newb pushing buttons.
    </small></font></p>
    <p><small><font face="Arial">&nbsp;</font></small></td>
  </tr>
